# Frontend Design System

Design for trust, clarity, and operator confidence.
Build interfaces that feel like a high-trust operations dashboard (Vercel, Linear, Stripe), not a flashy AI landing page.

## Typography Hierarchy

Use these exact classes. Do not invent new sizes.

- Page title: `text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground`
- Page subtitle: `mt-1 text-[13px] text-muted-foreground`
- Section / card title: `text-sm font-medium text-foreground`
- Body text: `text-[13px] text-foreground`
- Table cell text: `text-[13px]` (font-medium for primary column, regular for others)
- Labels and captions: `text-[11px] text-muted-foreground`
- Table headers: `text-[11px] font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground`
- Monetary and numeric values: add `tabular-nums` (and `font-mono` for IDs/keys)

## Spacing Scale

- Page-level wrapper: `space-y-6`
- Settings / multi-section pages: `space-y-8`
- Card internal padding: `p-4` (compact) or `p-6` (spacious)
- Stat card grids: `grid grid-cols-3 gap-3 p-4`
- Section gap within a card: `space-y-4`
- Form field gap: `space-y-1.5` (label to input), `space-y-4` (between fields)

## Color Usage

These are the only status/semantic colors. Do not add new ones.

- Normal text: `text-foreground`
- Secondary text: `text-muted-foreground`
- Success / healthy: `text-emerald-400`, `bg-emerald-500`
- Warning / at-risk (>=70% budget): `text-amber-400`, `bg-amber-500`
- Danger / critical (>=90% budget): `text-red-400`, `bg-red-500`
- Error banners: `border-red-500/20 bg-red-500/5 text-red-400`
- Default progress / primary: `bg-primary`

## Component Patterns

### Page Layout

Every dashboard page follows this structure:

```
<div className="space-y-6">
  {/* Header */}
  <div>
    <h1 className="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground">Title</h1>
    <p className="mt-1 text-[13px] text-muted-foreground">Subtitle.</p>
  </div>

  {/* Optional: filters / tabs */}
  {/* Optional: summary stat cards */}
  {/* Main content: card-wrapped table, list, or form */}
</div>
```

Settings pages add `mx-auto max-w-3xl` and use `space-y-8`.

### Cards

- Border: `border-border/50 bg-card`
- Header with action button: `flex flex-row items-center justify-between pb-4`
- Table inside card: table starts after `border-t border-border/30`, no outer card border on table

### Tables

- Container: `overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-border/50 bg-card`
- Header row: `border-border/50 hover:bg-transparent`
- Body rows: `border-border/30 transition-colors hover:bg-accent/40`
- Primary cell (linked): `text-[13px] font-medium text-foreground hover:text-primary`
- Secondary cells: `text-xs text-muted-foreground`

### Empty States

Centered layout with icon, title, and optional CTA:

```
<div className="flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4 rounded-lg border border-dashed border-border/50 py-20 text-center">
  <div className="flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-secondary/50">
    <Icon className="h-5 w-5 text-muted-foreground" />
  </div>
  <div>
    <p className="text-sm font-medium text-foreground">Title</p>
    <p className="mt-1 text-xs text-muted-foreground">Description.</p>
  </div>
  {/* Optional CTA button */}
</div>
```

### Stat Cards

```
<div className="rounded-lg border border-border/30 bg-background p-3">
  <p className="text-lg font-semibold tabular-nums text-foreground">Value</p>
  <p className="text-[11px] text-muted-foreground">Label</p>
</div>
```

### Loading Skeletons

Use `<Skeleton className="h-12 w-full rounded-lg bg-secondary/50" />` stacked with `space-y-2`.

### Buttons

- Primary CTA in card headers: `inline-flex h-8 items-center gap-1.5 rounded-md bg-primary px-3 text-xs font-medium text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90`
- Use `<Button size="sm">` for dialog footers
- Cancel buttons in dialogs: `inline-flex h-8 ... border border-border/50 bg-secondary`

### Dialogs

- Always include `DialogTitle` and `DialogDescription`
- Form fields use `Label className="text-xs text-muted-foreground"`
- Inputs: `h-9 border-border/50 bg-background text-[13px]`

## Avoid

- Purple gradients, neon glows, glassmorphism
- Over-rounded cards, cluttered KPI walls, decorative noise
- Equal visual weight on every element
- Placeholder lorem ipsum or vague labels
- Inventing new font sizes, colors, or spacing outside this system

## Design Workflow

- When building a new page, follow the Page Layout pattern above.
- Reference `app/(dashboard)/app/inbox/page.tsx` as the visual standard for list pages.
- Reference `app/(dashboard)/app/settings/page.tsx` as the standard for form/config pages.
- If a page is design-heavy, propose 2 concise visual directions before implementing.
- Budget and cost states must be scannable at a glance.
- Normal states feel calm; warning/danger states feel urgent.
